# My Custom Shell (CodeCrafters)

A simple Unix shell implementation in C.

## Base Stages:
- [x] Prompting `$`
- [x] REPL loop
- [x] Builtins: `echo`, `exit`, `type`
- [x] Executing external programs (`fork`, `execvp`, `wait`)

## What I learned:
I learned how to create a `REPL loop`, how to work with `environmental variables` (PATH) and how `OS manages processes`. Hardest Challenge was understanding how PATH , `fork()` and `execvp()` work
